paragraphs.title: make dataset, function
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
from pyspark.ml.feature import StringIndexer
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler
from pyspark.ml.pipeline import Pipeline
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml.clustering import KMeans
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from pyspark.sql import functions
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import (StringType, IntegerType, DoubleType)

df_cleandays = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///dayday/clean_days.parquet')
df_nt = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/nt_srs.parquet')\
             .where('date >= "2017-04-12"')

# 몇 CCT 단위로 짜를건지 정해야함! --------
udf_classify_cct = udf(lambda cct: int(cct/500)*500, IntegerType())


def get_daily_cct_(spdf, date: str, return_type='list'):
    print(date)
    tmpdf = spdf.where('date == "%s"' % date)\
                .select('date', 'time', 'cct')
    tmplist = tmpdf.collect()
    
    left_idx, right_idx = 0, 0
    
    # find min value index of left and right
    for i in range(1, 120):
        if tmplist[left_idx][2] > tmplist[i][2]:
            # print(i, ':', tmplist[left_idx][2], '>', tmplist[i][2])
            left_idx = i
        
    for i in range(len(tmplist) - 120, len(tmplist)):
        if tmplist[right_idx][2] > tmplist[i][2]:
            # print(i, ':', tmplist[right_idx][2], '>', tmplist[i][2])
            right_idx = i

    if return_type == 'list':
        return tmpdf.collect()[left_idx:right_idx]
    else:  # return_type == 'spdf':
        return sc.parallelize(tmpdf.collect()[left_idx:right_idx]).toDF()


def get_freq_dist_spdf(day):
    return get_daily_cct_(df_nt, day, 'spdf')\
                     .drop('date', 'time')\
                     .withColumn('cct_group', udf_classify_cct('cct'))\
                     .groupby('cct_group').agg({'cct': 'count'}).sort('cct_group')\
                     .withColumnRenamed('count(cct)', day)


clean_days = list(map(lambda s: s['date'], df_cleandays.collect()))

paragraphs.title: clustering example
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

# 원본데이터
# http://data.seoul.go.kr/dataList/datasetView.do?infId=OA-1218&srvType=S&serviceKind=1&currentPageNo=1
# 서울시 공공와이파이 위치정보 (영어)

d1 = spark.read.option("header", "true") \
    .option("sep", ",") \
    .option("inferSchema", True) \
    .option("mode", "DROPMALFORMED") \
    .csv("file:///home/witlab/wifi.csv")

d1.printSchema()

d2 = d1.toDF("number", "name", "SI", "GOO", "DONG", "x", "y", "b_code", "h_code", "utmk_x", "utmk_y", "wtm_x", "wtm_y")

d3 = d2.select(d2.GOO.alias("loc"), d2.x, d2.y)

d3.show(5, False)

indexer = StringIndexer(inputCol="loc", outputCol="loccode")

assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=["loccode", "x", "y"], outputCol="features")

kmeans = KMeans(k=5, seed=1, featuresCol="features")

pipeline = Pipeline(stages=[indexer, assembler, kmeans])

model = pipeline.fit(d3)

d4 = model.transform(d3)

d4.groupBy("prediction") \
    .agg(functions.collect_set("loc").alias("loc")) \
    .orderBy("prediction").show(100, False)

WSSSE = model.stages[2].computeCost(d4)
print("Within Set Sum of Squared Errors = %d" % WSSSE)

print("Cluster Centers: ")
for v in model.stages[2].clusterCenters():
    print(v)
